# Backend Rules

## Supabase
- All DB access goes through `src/lib/supabase/` — never import supabase client directly in components
- Use the server client (`createServerClient`) in Server Components and Route Handlers
- Use the browser client (`createBrowserClient`) only in Client Components
- Row Level Security (RLS) must be enabled on every table — no exceptions
- Never expose the service role key to the client

## API Route Handlers (`app/api/`)
- Every route handler must validate input with zod before processing
- Return consistent JSON shape: `{ data, error, message }`
- HTTP status codes must be correct — 200, 201, 400, 401, 403, 404, 500
- Rate limit sensitive routes (order creation, auth)

## Database
- All schema changes go through Supabase migrations (`supabase/migrations/`) — never edit tables manually in the dashboard during dev
- Foreign keys must have proper `ON DELETE` behaviour defined
- Index columns that are frequently filtered (`category_id`, `status`, `created_at`)

## Image uploads (Cloudinary)
- Upload happens server-side in an API route — never expose Cloudinary API secret to browser
- Store only the Cloudinary public URL in the database, never the raw file
- Transform images at the URL level (`c_fill,w_800,h_800,q_auto,f_auto`) — no client-side resizing
